<p>
Mailmark is a two-dimensional (2D) barcode type used by the Royal Mail, the national postal service of the United Kingdom. It serves to track and sort mail in a more efficient way. Such barcodes are used to store specific information about a postal item, such as the service level and the destination country, in addition to the sender and recipient information. Mailmark barcodes can be scanned by special readers, which can process barcodes more quickly and accurately than traditional barcode scanners. Mailmark barcodes can be placed on letters or packages and allow improving the efficiency of the Royal Mail's mail sorting process by ensuring that mail is delivered to the correct location in a timely manner.
